reviews.review_text: First trip to the OMNI Rode down with my friend Pugs and absolutely had the time of my life. Driving hundreds of miles from Virginia to see a band was still new for me. Greensboro that followed was awesome too. Ramrod came to our room to procure something from a brother in our clan, so I was told... it all seems so surreal at this point.  What I do remember was Foolish Heart instantly becoming one of my favorite tunes. Franklin's > Stranger was fun, but now I see how special it really was. The band was at peak form for this show netting a High-5 from me.
